summary: An FBI Special Agent from the New York Child Exploitation & Human Trafficking Task Force sends a grand jury subpoena to an organization regarding a child exploitation/human trafficking investigation, requesting expedited compliance by February 7, 2020, and asking that the subscriber not be notified.

persons.name: Special Agent FBI New York Child Exploitation & Human Trafficking
persons.context: The FBI agent who sent the email correspondence attaching a federal grand jury subpoena and requesting expedited cooperation in a child exploitation/human trafficking investigation.

events.title: Subpoena Compliance Deadline
events.description: The due date for the organization to comply with the federal grand jury subpoena.
personsInvolved: Special Agent FBI New York Child Exploitation & Human Trafficking

keyFacts: A federal grand jury subpoena was issued in a child exploitation/human trafficking investigation.
The subpoena was sent to an organization with an expedited due date of February 7, 2020.
The FBI requested that the organization not notify the subscriber due to the sensitive nature of the investigation.
